{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-markdown-remark-frontmatter-slug-js","path":"/projects/covid-clicker/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Cookie Clicker meets Covid?</h1>\n<h2>Tldr;</h2>\n<p>If you're Gen Z, then you've probably heard of the game Cookie Clicker and played it during ICT/DIT\nclass. I've taken that, and used it as a base for trying out the css animation library, Animation.css.</p>\n<h2>What was this all for?</h2>\n<p>I decided to make an idle based game because I wanted to play around with the\n<a href=\"https://animate.style\">Animation.css</a> library. I'd heard positive things about it, but hadn't\ngotten to use it yet. If you're wondering what it is, it's a library that provides utility classes\nwith a wide array of animations.</p>\n<h2>The game in a nut shell</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 788px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/18d170d13c3e7b61b586967d86f89bcf/ea7fb/covid-clicker.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 231%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"covid-clicker game\"\n        title=\"covid-clicker game\"\n        src=\"/static/18d170d13c3e7b61b586967d86f89bcf/ea7fb/covid-clicker.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/18d170d13c3e7b61b586967d86f89bcf/772e8/covid-clicker.png 200w,\n/static/18d170d13c3e7b61b586967d86f89bcf/e17e5/covid-clicker.png 400w,\n/static/18d170d13c3e7b61b586967d86f89bcf/ea7fb/covid-clicker.png 788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Arrive on the main screen and admire the neat artwork (credit someone else)</li>\n<li>Click on the world to infect a person (community case)</li>\n<li>Purchase spreaders in the shop which will increase the number of community cases per second.</li>\n<li>Further increase the spread with upgrades like mutating the virus.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Animating the clicks</h2>\n<p>What I wanted to do, was make clicking the world addictive. When clicking, a little covid image\nappears, and floats off.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/e0885/covid-animation.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 83%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"covid-clicker animation\"\n        title=\"covid-clicker animation\"\n        src=\"/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/5a190/covid-animation.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/772e8/covid-animation.png 200w,\n/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/e17e5/covid-animation.png 400w,\n/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/5a190/covid-animation.png 800w,\n/static/082c9a6cef1a11e1b8a4da5d1a648962/e0885/covid-animation.png 918w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This works by</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Clicking the world registers an on click event.</li>\n<li>Event handler on the click adds a float object to an array which contains the x and y position\nof the click.</li>\n<li>Ephemeral components are created for each object in the array of floaters. These components are\nabsolute positioned, with an x, y position of the click.</li>\n<li>I added the animation.css classes <code>animate__animated animate__slow animate__fadeOutUp</code> which gives\nthem a fading upwards effect.</li>\n<li>Every 15 seconds, I clear the array of objects so I don't have a memory leak.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Check it out</h2>\n<p>This project is open source, you can check it out on my github. <a href=\"https://github.com/IsaacMurtagh/covid-clicker\">https://github.com/IsaacMurtagh/covid-clicker</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"August 30, 2021","slug":"/projects/covid-clicker/","title":"Covid Clicker","tags":["Vue3","animation.css","Open source"]}}},"pageContext":{"id":"3002178c-ecdf-5d98-b83e-8d776bf27be8","frontmatter__slug":"/projects/covid-clicker/","__params":{"frontmatter__slug":"projects"}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}